The paper deals with the recovery of sparse signal vectors, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and statistical inference (cs.SI). The use of compressed sensing techniques also suggests that cs.IT and cs.SP are likely categories. The focus on improving the performance of existing algorithms suggests that cs.LG and cs.NA are also possible categories.
